<!--
source: core/templates — copy to `.claude/CLAUDE.local.md` in a target project.

CLAUDE.local.md is the per-developer, uncommitted overrides file.
Gitignored. Purpose: your personal context that doesn't belong in the
shared `.claude/CLAUDE.md`.

Use this for:
  - Local service URLs (http://localhost:8080 vs the prod domain)
  - Your personal working notes about this project
  - Temporary reminders while you're heads-down on a feature
  - Credentials hints (NEVER actual credentials — just "token is in 1Password 'foo'")
  - "Currently debugging X; if Claude notices Y, it's related"

Do NOT use this for:
  - Actual secrets — those belong in env vars / your secrets manager
  - Rules the whole team should follow — those go in rules/ (shared)
  - Project-wide architecture notes — those go in CLAUDE.md (shared)
-->

# Local overrides for <project>

## Environment

- API runs locally at: http://localhost:<port>
- DB: <local container name / connection hint>
- Secrets: see `~/.env.<project>` (gitignored)

## Current focus

<!-- Replace with whatever you're working on. Claude will pick this up. -->

- Working on: <ticket / feature / bug>
- Open threads: <thing you'll come back to>

## Personal preferences for this project

<!-- e.g. -->
- When I ask for "the usual test run", I mean `pytest tests/unit -x`.
- Don't auto-run migrations in this project; I run them manually.
- Prefer `uv run` over activating the venv.
